description:
## Overview

Wire up QML to use ProRes proxy for playback, auto-skip cut regions, and display crops via QML clipping. All preview is non-destructive.

## Critical: Consistent Time Display

**The UI must always show effective time (post-cuts), not source time.**

Example with 10s video, cut at 3-4s:
- Video player position 5000ms (source) → display "4.0s" (effective)
- Duration display: "9.0s" (not 10s)
- Timeline length: 9 seconds
- Seeking to "6s" on timeline → seeks to source 7s

### Playhead Position
```qml
Text {
    // WRONG: text: (video.position / 1000).toFixed(1) + "s"
    // RIGHT:
    text: (session.sourceToEffective(video.position / 1000)).toFixed(1) + "s"
}
```

### Timeline Interactions
```qml
MouseArea {
    onClicked: function(mouse) {
        // User clicks at effective time position
        var effectiveTime = (mouse.x / width) * session.effectiveDuration
        // Convert to source time for seeking
        var sourceTime = session.effectiveToSource(effectiveTime)
        video.position = sourceTime * 1000
    }
}
```

### Applying New Cuts
```qml
// User drags to select cut region in timeline (effective time)
onCutRequested: function(effectiveStart, effectiveEnd) {
    // Convert to source time before sending to backend
    var sourceStart = session.effectiveToSource(effectiveStart)
    var sourceEnd = session.effectiveToSource(effectiveEnd)
    session.applyCut(sourceStart, sourceEnd)
}
```

## Proxy Playback

```qml
Video {
    source: session.proxyReady ? session.proxyVideoUrl : session.sourceVideoUrl
}
```

## Auto-Skip Cut Regions

```qml
Video {
    id: videoPlayer
    property var cutRegions: session.cutRegions  // [{start, end}] in ms, SOURCE time

    onPositionChanged: {
        for (var i = 0; i < cutRegions.length; i++) {
            var cut = cutRegions[i]
            if (position >= cut.start && position < cut.end) {
                position = cut.end  // Skip to end of cut
                break
            }
        }
    }
}
```

## Crop Preview via QML Clipping

```qml
Item {
    clip: true
    width: displayCropWidth
    height: displayCropHeight

    Video {
        x: -cropX * scale
        y: -cropY * scale
        width: proxyWidth * scale
        height: proxyHeight * scale
    }
}
```

## Cut Visualization in Timeline

Cut regions shown at their **effective** positions (they collapse the timeline):

```qml
// Cuts don't take space in effective timeline - they're the gaps
// Optionally show cut markers at cut points
Repeater {
    model: session.cutRegions
    Rectangle {
        // Show a thin line where the cut occurred (in effective time)
        x: timeToX(session.sourceToEffective(modelData.start))
        width: 2
        color: "#ff4444"
    }
}
```

## Bridge Properties

```python
@Property(float, notify=editPlanChanged)
def effectiveDuration(self) -> float:
    """Duration after cuts applied - use for timeline length."""
    source_dur = self._session.source_duration
    return self._session.edit_plan.effective_duration(source_dur)

@Slot(float, result=float)
def sourceToEffective(self, source_ms: float) -> float:
    """Convert source time (ms) to effective time (ms) for display."""
    return self._session.edit_plan.source_to_effective(source_ms / 1000) * 1000

@Slot(float, result=float)  
def effectiveToSource(self, effective_ms: float) -> float:
    """Convert effective time (ms) to source time (ms) for seeking/cuts."""
    return self._session.edit_plan.effective_to_source(effective_ms / 1000) * 1000
```

## Files to Modify

- `VideoArea.qml`: Proxy source, auto-skip, crop clipping
- `Timeline.qml`: Effective time display, time conversions
- `CutBar.qml`: Cut visualization, effective time conversions
- `TransportControls.qml`: Position display in effective time
- `bridge.py`: Time conversion slots, effectiveDuration property

## Testing

- GUI test: Position display matches effective time
- GUI test: Duration shows effective (post-cut) length
- GUI test: Seeking via timeline works correctly with cuts
- GUI test: Playback auto-skips cut regions
- GUI test: New cuts applied at correct source positions
- GUI test: Multiple stacked cuts handled correctly

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All time displays show effective time
- [ ] Timeline length matches effective duration
- [ ] Seeking converts effective → source correctly
- [ ] New cuts convert effective → source before applying
- [ ] Stacked cuts work correctly
- [ ] Auto-skip works in source time coordinates
- [ ] Crop clipping displays correctly
